       #include <fp.h> #include <math.h> #include <stdio.h>

       enum fp_class_type fp_class(double x);

       int isnan(double x);

       double copysign(double x, double y);

       double scalbn(double x, int n);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       Most  of  these functions provide capabilities required by
       ANSI/IEEE Std 754-1985 or suggested in its appendix.

       fp_class(x) corresponds to the IEEE's class() and  classi-
       fies x as zero, subnormal, normal, oo, or quiet or signal-
       ing   NaN;   /usr/ucbinclude/sys/ieeefp.h   defines   enum
       fp_class_type.   The  following  function returns 0 if the
       indicated condition is not satisfied: returns 1  if  x  is
       NaN

       copysign(x,y) returns x with y's sign bit.

       scalbn(x,n) returns x* 2**n computed by exponent manipula-
       tion rather than by actually performing an  exponentiation
       or  a multiplication.  Thus 1 <= scalbn(fabs(x),-ilogb(x))
       < 2

       for every x except 0, oo, and NaN.

